cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for semantic mapping of remote sensing images using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of dense dilated convolutions and the fusion of local and global context information, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed network to remote sensing images also involves the use of geographic information systems (GIS) and image processing (cs.GR), and the network can potentially be used for autonomous navigation and robotics (cs.RO).
